<a name="week0"><b>0: Overture</b> 
</big><br>


<p>
Reading:
<ul>
<li> <a href="../resources/index.shtml#risks">Neumann</a>, 1.1-1.4, 3.  
(Nice overview of the breadth of issues, with many real examples.)
<li> <a href="../resources/index.shtml#craft">S&amp;M</a>, Chapter 1.
<li> <a href="../resources/index.shtml#craft">S&amp;M</a>, 6.0-6.3.
<li> <a href="../resources/index.shtml#aleph1">Aleph One</a>. The classic stack-smashing paper.
</ul>

<p>
Lecture notes:
<ul>
<li> <a href="mar28/index.shtml"><b>Wed, March 28: Introduction.</b></a>
<li> Thu, March 29 (X-hour). <i>(Open)</i>
<li> <a href="mar30/index.shtml"><b>Fri, March 30: Blunders.</b></a>
</ul>


